      "span_text": "In addition, prostate cancer is well suited for oncolytic adenoviral therapy due to easy delivery of adenovirus into the intraprostate, allowing high titers of adenovirus to infect tumor cells without dissemination to other sites. [CITATION_4] The adenovirus replication results in release of progeny viruses to infect adjacent tumor cells, leading to amplification of input virus.",
